(power_register, power_pad).explanation: Register file power consumption and I/O pad power consumption are independent components of total processor power, with no direct causal relationship between them;

(power_register, time).explanation: Register file power consumption does not directly cause changes in execution time, as both are influenced by workload characteristics and design parameters independently;

(power_register, power_clock).explanation: Register file power and clock distribution power are separate power domains in processor design with no direct causal relationship;
